1775844516104471	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3nww		item.create	bn-3j0q	{"description":"After bn-pu4y/bn-30ub/bn-3f00 shipped, no bone has yet measured the full 'bn triage' pipeline end-to-end against the SQLite fixture. The isolated benches (normalize + pagerank) summed to ~16 ms at 10k, but the path also does RawGraph::from_sqlite (HashMap<String, NodeIndex> build), build_item_to_scc_map, GraphStats, composite_score aggregation, and any triage_support code in bones-cli. We need to measure the whole thing on the Tier M fixture and see whether the next real hot spot is in code we've touched or somewhere else entirely.\n\nPlan:\n1. Extend crates/bones-core/benches/large_repo.rs (or add a new bench in bones-triage that shares the fixture) to call the full pipeline against the Tier M SQLite DB.\n2. Report end-to-end latency at Tier M (50k events, 10k items).\n3. If > 30 ms, profile with scripts/flamegraph.sh triage and report the top 3 hot frames.\n4. If the win surface is zero, document and close. If there's a clear target, file a follow-up bone for it.\n\nExit: numbers committed to benches/BASELINE.md and either a fresh bone or a documented close.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","measurement"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"End-to-end triage bench + next-hotspot scan"}	blake3:vWI-8wZ5BrkLLgzVYL17R_YQO5C4occDwlg8ssZRxtY
