1775845344276360	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3pgw		item.comment	bn-2qbr	{"body":"Measurements complete, merged as benches/RELEASE_PROFILE.md. Leaving bone in 'doing' state pending user decision.\n\nSummary:\n- opt-level=\"z\" 28.92 MB → opt-level=3 thin-LTO 34.62 MB (+19.7%)\n- Startup / 100-item triage: noise (~5%)\n- At 10k+ items: criterion benches already at opt-level=3 show 2x-25x wins that users currently don't get under shipped release profile\n\nRecommendation: flip. Exact diff in RELEASE_PROFILE.md §Recommendation.\n\nTo execute the flip: edit [profile.release] to {opt-level=3, lto=\"thin\", codegen-units=16, panic=\"abort\", strip=true}, delete [profile.release-fast]. Then 'just check' and 'just install' to verify, and ship."}	blake3:_7nNZOy0HI07T1EsieDYdztFqPaj-2wqLYnqNqU8v58
1775943233567589	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3pww		item.move	bn-2qbr	{"state":"done"}	blake3:2tl_KYy6rivpiETvwnPUxT7VcnPVGt-WPRHkWElZQaE
1775961446878035	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3qAw		item.comment	bn-3mof	{"body":"Closing as out-of-scope for the bn-1582 perf pass. Frecency is a product/ranking feature, not a performance optimization — it adds functionality rather than making existing functionality faster.\n\nKey reasons for deferral rather than implementation:\n\n1. **Determinism loss.** Current triage scoring is deterministic and reproducible: same events → same scores for every agent viewing the same repo. Frecency makes ranking depend on per-user viewing history, breaking 'did we both see the same top-5 bone?' coordination between agents.\n\n2. **New persistent state.** Needs a store (.bones/frecency.db or sqlite rows) tracking (agent, item, last_access_us, access_count) for every bone every agent touches — reads from bn show, hovers in the TUI, etc. That's surface area across the entire CLI.\n\n3. **Not a perf issue.** The bn-2ury baseline showed composite_score at 10k items costs 119 µs. Adding a sixth frecency term wouldn't move any latency needle. The fff.nvim technique was originally interesting because we thought triage was slow — now that triage/10k is 18 ms end-to-end, there's no perf justification.\n\n4. **UX design call.** Where does the frecency bonus plug into composite_score? As a sixth weighted term (zeta * F)? What weight? Does it apply to bn next / bn triage / TUI list / all three? Per-agent or global? These are product decisions that deserve their own goal with sub-tasks for storage design, UI surface, score composition, and per-agent scoping.\n\nIf frecency is still wanted, recommend filing as a fresh kind=goal outside the bn-1582 perf pass, with child tasks for: (a) storage design, (b) instrumentation surface (which CLI paths record accesses), (c) composite_score integration + weight tuning, (d) per-agent vs global policy. That's a week of design work, not a perf bone."}	blake3:bvE_eFGo4phbVYCyrHIm0WRl7AVoyedERkX7MR-ZFW8
1775961446902260	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3qQw		item.move	bn-3mof	{"state":"done"}	blake3:hAnGxFGSltvaFiGLfioPytSDttwP_j19lulV6SryJ0Q
