1777247701886755	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3uww		item.create	bn-vtf3	{"description":"Today `bn doctor --fix` repairs projection drift and stale symlinks but does NOT regenerate missing sealed-shard manifests — users must run `bn verify --regenerate-missing` as a separate step.\n\nObserved in two projects (~/src/bones, ~/src/chief) where the 2026-02 sealed shard had no manifest, likely because the validate-on-startup feature (5809c3dd, 2026-03-04) didn't backfill manifests for shards sealed under the older code path. Both projects flunked startup integrity checks until `bn verify --regenerate-missing` was run by hand.\n\nRepro:\n1. Open a project whose oldest sealed shard predates the validate-on-startup feature.\n2. `bn doctor` reports `shard_integrity FAIL: missing manifest`.\n3. `bn doctor --fix` does not repair it.\n4. `bn verify --regenerate-missing` does repair it (manifest is purely derived: event_count + byte_len + blake3(file), so regen is non-destructive).\n\nProposed fix: when `bn doctor --fix` encounters a sealed shard with a missing manifest, call into the same regen logic that `bn verify --regenerate-missing` uses (verify/mod.rs already gates this on a `regenerate_missing: bool` parameter — wire `--fix` to set it to true). Optionally also surface a doctor-level note that the regen happened, distinct from the existing 'projection rebuilt' / 'symlink removed' fix outputs.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `bn doctor --fix` on a project with a missing sealed-shard manifest writes the manifest and reports it as a fix.\n- A subsequent `bn doctor` (no --fix) passes integrity check.\n- Existing `bn verify --regenerate-missing` continues to work standalone.","kind":"task","title":"wire --regenerate-missing into 'bn doctor --fix'"}	blake3:dfCIpMwfSlewUi0jE3WsoSfpUvMn1CXwxg900WspurQ
1777249160171424	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3vAw		item.move	bn-vtf3	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:j5QptArnnqgytiRlGGdLMaCfKjvEcQHzD-MJAXlkkwY
1777249160180764	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3vQw		item.assign	bn-vtf3	{"action":"assign","agent":"bones-dev"}	blake3:5RovQnqn_K_zS2EQdfQRteDpxLJ5mgw5k3cjQ-34jss
1777252645644141	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3vgw		item.comment	bn-vtf3	{"body":"Re-scoped: `bn doctor --fix` already regenerates missing manifests via verify_repository(bones_dir, fix). Verified empirically with a forged broken shard. The real UX gap is that the `shard_integrity` FAIL output doesn't hint at `--fix` like `projection_drift` and `stale_symlink` do. Fix is now: append 'run with --fix to regenerate missing manifests' to shard_integrity details when applicable."}	blake3:0zORyMRGwfz7RGTtaI_I4mTtq2ltalI7rFwNSkCM5LQ
1777253055581033	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3vww		item.move	bn-vtf3	{"state":"done"}	blake3:FERKv68H1T5CNEI-lCFBMFMaObvzY9BJnEGoNhNhbqw
1777254992150814	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3wAw		item.create	bn-11q8	{"description":"Default `bones-cli` to mimalloc as global allocator so `just install` ships a binary that does not exhibit glibc-malloc arena fragmentation in long-running TUI sessions. Diagnosed in ward (1.35GB RSS, 6GB VmHWM, 113 displayed bones / 1225 total) — three large glibc per-thread arenas held memory that mimalloc would have decommitted via madvise(DONTNEED).\n\nImplementation:\n- Add `mimalloc` to bones-cli default features.\n- Make the `mimalloc` global_allocator cfg yield when `jemalloc` or `dhat-heap` is selected, so users who opt into a profiling/alternative allocator do not need `--no-default-features`.\n- Document the precedence in the feature comments.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `just install` produces a `bn` binary linked against mimalloc.\n- `cargo build --features jemalloc` still produces a single-allocator binary using jemalloc.\n- `cargo build --features dhat-heap` still produces a dhat-instrumented binary.\n- All existing tests pass.","kind":"task","title":"make mimalloc default in bn binary"}	blake3:tXEThp4LMEJL6rMIaE6IFjCO19-fVyeMVOGTqEdWOgQ
1777254995825049	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3wQw		item.move	bn-11q8	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:NdUim5R2tpih8Jg3KxvcZp2lxD1mCnW3sgYe0w0Mi1c
