1777325641358071	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3yAw		item.create	bn-2tuc	{"description":"**File**: crates/bones-cli/src/tui/actions.rs:52-72, 110-130, 198-201, 267-270, 497-500; crates/bones-core/src/shard.rs:480-500, 560-570\n\n**Issue**: TUI mutating actions compute `wall_ts_us`, assign ITC, hash the event, and only then call `ShardManager::append`, so event identity is created outside the repo-wide shard lock.\n\n**Root Cause**: The CLI write path acquires `ShardLock`, rotates, calls `next_timestamp`, assigns ITC, hashes, and uses `append_raw` while still holding the lock. The TUI helper path calls `next_timestamp` before any explicit lock, then calls `append`, which acquires the lock and advances the monotonic clock again without updating the already-hashed event.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P1 (data integrity risk under concurrent writers)\n- Scope: TUI do/done/create/update/comment/link/unlink/move actions\n- Reproducibility: Timing-dependent; reproducible when a TUI write races with another TUI or CLI write\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\nlet ts = shard_mgr.next_timestamp().context(\"get timestamp\")?;\nlet mut event = Event { wall_ts_us: ts, ... };\nassign_next_itc(project_root, &mut event)?;\nlet line = writer::write_event(&mut event).context(\"serialize event\")?;\nshard_mgr.append(&line, false, Duration::from_secs(5))?;\n```\n\n```rust\n/// The caller must hold the repo lock.\npub fn next_timestamp(&self) -> Result<i64, ShardError> { ... }\n\npub fn append(...) -> Result<i64, ShardError> {\n    let _lock = ShardLock::acquire(&self.lock_path(), lock_timeout)?;\n    let ts = self.next_timestamp()?;\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n**Context**: `ListView` calls these helpers for every TUI mutation. A concurrent CLI command can append a later event while the TUI event is already timestamped but not yet appended, causing shard append order and event timestamps/ITC state to disagree. The append-only event log and CRDT/LWW behavior depend on these event identities being generated atomically with the write.\n\n**Related**: The CLI create path in `crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/create.rs:749-779` performs the same operations under `ShardLock`, which highlights the inconsistency.","kind":"bug","labels":["race-condition","data-integrity","fresh-eyes"],"size":"m","title":"TUI writes event timestamps and ITC outside shard lock","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:YkJj_QFescyH3w0Q1waH5xG7fH3IxcOl3MvN5ojIcYo
1777325654966832	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3yQw		item.create	bn-lu0a	{"description":"**File**: crates/bones-cli/src/tui/list/data.rs:8; crates/bones-cli/src/tui/actions.rs:54-72; crates/bones-cli/src/validate.rs:182-209; crates/bones-core/src/event/writer.rs:76-82\n\n**Issue**: The TUI resolves an agent identity but never validates it before writing events, so whitespace from `BONES_AGENT`/`AGENT` can be serialized directly into TSJSON structural fields.\n\n**Root Cause**: CLI mutating commands call `validate::validate_agent`, which rejects empty, overlong, and whitespace-containing agent values. `ListView::new` stores `agent::require_agent(None).unwrap_or_else(|_| \"tui\".to_string())` directly, and TUI action helpers copy that string into `Event.agent`. The event writer validates only the JSON payload newline invariant before formatting the agent between tab delimiters.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P1 (append-only log corruption risk)\n- Scope: Every TUI mutation when the resolved environment agent contains a tab or newline; space-containing agents also bypass CLI's documented validation\n- Reproducibility: 100% with an invalid TUI agent identity such as an `AGENT` value containing a tab or newline\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\nlet agent = agent::require_agent(None).unwrap_or_else(|_| \"tui\".to_string());\n```\n\n```rust\nlet mut event = Event {\n    wall_ts_us: ts,\n    agent: agent.to_string(),\n    ...\n};\n```\n\n```rust\nif s.chars().any(char::is_whitespace) {\n    return Err(ValidationError::new(...));\n}\n```\n\n```rust\nOk(format!(\n    \"{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\",\n    event.wall_ts_us,\n    event.agent,\n    event.itc,\n    ...\n))\n```\n\n**Context**: TSJSON parsing expects exactly eight tab-separated fields. If the TUI writes an agent containing a tab, the next replay sees the wrong field count; if it contains a newline, the writer emits an extra physical line. CLI paths reject these identities before writing, so the risk is specific to TUI mutations and any other direct writer path that bypasses CLI validation.\n\n**Related**: `crates/bones-core/src/event/parser.rs:381-422` documents that full parse rejects whitespace in agent fields, but the writer path can still produce invalid lines because it does not validate the field before formatting.","kind":"bug","labels":["data-loss","validation","fresh-eyes"],"size":"s","title":"TUI accepts invalid agent identities that can corrupt TSJSON events","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:CEOjHNmzw4XWyy594qmwHvCYeL2BiI-x4s0ysjMBgFU
1777325667981140	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3ygw		item.create	bn-1wex	{"description":"**File**: crates/bones-cli/src/tui/list/input.rs:829-850; crates/bones-core/src/db/project.rs:433-452; crates/bones-core/src/crdt/item_state.rs:343-365; crates/bones-core/src/compact.rs:267-282\n\n**Issue**: Label replacement events encoded as a JSON array update SQLite labels, but the CRDT `WorkItemState` ignores the same event shape.\n\n**Root Cause**: The TUI edit modal emits one `item.update` with `field = \"labels\"` and `value = json!(draft.labels)`. The SQLite projector explicitly supports array values as a legacy full replacement. The CRDT item-state replay only handles object values with `{\"action\":\"add\"|\"remove\",\"label\":...}` and treats array values as no-ops.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (projection/CRDT divergence and possible label loss in CRDT-derived workflows)\n- Scope: TUI edit-label saves and any historical legacy label replacement events\n- Reproducibility: 100% for a `labels` update event whose value is an array\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\n(\"labels\".to_string(), json!(draft.labels)),\n```\n\n```rust\nif let Some(labels) = data.value.as_array() {\n    self.conn.execute(\"DELETE FROM item_labels WHERE item_id = ?1\", ...)?;\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n```rust\n\"labels\" => {\n    // Labels update via OR-Set add/remove encoded in value.\n    if let Some(obj) = data.value.as_object() {\n        let action = obj.get(\"action\").and_then(|v| v.as_str()).unwrap_or(\"\");\n        ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Context**: `compact_item` replays events into `WorkItemState` before creating a snapshot payload. Any label replacement event that exists in SQLite after projection is absent from that CRDT state, so CRDT-derived compaction, convergence tests, and state-based graph/materialization paths can disagree with the normal SQLite projection for the same event log.\n\n**Related**: The current CLI tag path in `crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/tag.rs:186-199` emits the object add/remove shape, so the divergence is specifically the legacy array shape still emitted by TUI edit and accepted by the SQLite projector.","kind":"bug","labels":["data-integrity","logic-error","fresh-eyes"],"size":"m","title":"Legacy label replacement events diverge between SQLite projection and CRDT state"}	blake3:ybhKLbVEDKakwHrTI53kkmi4CjOrvtUuYPPZyZAlo_8
1777325679843190	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3yww		item.create	bn-947m	{"description":"**File**: crates/bones-cli/src/tui/list/search.rs:51-57; crates/bones-cli/src/tui/list/input.rs:1244-1251; crates/bones-cli/src/tui/list/render.rs:1098-1114\n\n**Issue**: TUI slash search sets `search_refining = true` even when there is no semantic model and therefore no background refinement receiver to ever clear the flag.\n\n**Root Cause**: `refresh_semantic_search_ids` unconditionally marks the search as refining after tier-1 fast search. The only code that clears that flag after this point is the receiver polling path in `tick`, but `semantic_refinement_rx` is only installed inside `if let Some(model) = self.semantic_model.clone()`.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (persistent incorrect UI state)\n- Scope: TUI search in environments where semantic search is disabled or `SemanticModel::load()` failed\n- Reproducibility: 100% after any non-empty slash search with `semantic_model == None` and a successful fast search\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\n// Tier 2: spawn background thread for full semantic refinement.\nself.search_refining = true;\nif let Some(model) = self.semantic_model.clone() {\n    let (tx, rx) = std::sync::mpsc::channel();\n    self.semantic_refinement_rx = Some(rx);\n    std::thread::spawn(move || { ... });\n}\n```\n\n```rust\nif let Some(rx) = &self.semantic_refinement_rx\n    && let Ok(refined_ids) = rx.try_recv()\n{\n    self.semantic_search_ids = refined_ids;\n    self.semantic_refinement_rx = None;\n    self.search_refining = false;\n}\n```\n\n```rust\nlet refining_indicator = if app.search_refining { ... } else { String::new() };\n```\n\n**Context**: `ListView::new` sets `semantic_model` to `None` when semantic search is disabled by config or the model cannot be loaded. In that common fallback mode, tier-1 lexical/structural search still returns results, but the title bar keeps rendering the refinement indicator indefinitely because no refinement worker exists.","kind":"bug","labels":["logic-error","fresh-eyes"],"size":"xs","title":"TUI slash search shows perpetual refinement spinner without semantic model"}	blake3:pM7Y1jbDtKdGSHdldFUWtaHkOnQ8Ku7Zknagu8wginI
