1777330087052926	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE32Aw		item.create	bn-250m	{"description":"**File**: crates/bones-core/src/event/parser.rs:479-494\n\n**Issue**: `parse_line` verifies `event_hash` after parsing and canonicalizing the JSON payload instead of hashing the exact field 7 bytes from the TSJSON line.\n\n**Root Cause**: The parser's hash check rebuilds `canonical_data` from `data_json` and passes `&canonical_data` into `compute_event_hash`, even though the TSJSON format and writer define the hash input as fields 1-7 joined exactly as serialized.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (event integrity validation is weaker than documented)\n- Scope: All replay, rebuild, export, merge-driver, verification, and command paths that call `parse_line` or `parse_lines`\n- Reproducibility: 100% for a line whose JSON payload is semantically equivalent but byte-different from the canonical writer output\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\n// crates/bones-core/src/event/parser.rs:479-494\nlet canonical_data = serde_json::from_str::<serde_json::Value>(data_json)\n    .map(|v| canonicalize_json(&v))\n    .map_err(|e| ParseError::InvalidDataJson(e.to_string()))?;\nlet hash_fields: [&str; 7] = [\n    fields[0],\n    fields[1],\n    fields[2],\n    fields[3],\n    fields[4],\n    fields[5],\n    &canonical_data,\n];\nlet computed = compute_event_hash(&hash_fields);\n```\n\nThe writer documents and implements the hash input as the serialized fields, with field 7 already canonical when written:\n```rust\n// crates/bones-core/src/event/writer.rs:102-125\n/// `{wall_ts_us}\\t{agent}\\t{itc}\\t{parents}\\t{type}\\t{item_id}\\t{data_json}\\n`\nlet hash_input = format!(\n    \"{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\t{}\\n\",\n    event.wall_ts_us,\n    event.agent,\n    event.itc,\n    parents,\n    event.event_type,\n    event.item_id,\n    data_json,\n);\n```\n\n**Context**: `parse_line` is used by rebuild (`crates/bones-core/src/db/rebuild.rs:237`), export (`crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/export.rs:48`), log collection (`crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/log.rs:142`), undo event loading (`crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/undo.rs:140,193`), verification, cache loading, and the merge driver. Those paths will accept a non-canonical payload as long as its parsed JSON canonicalizes to the original value.\n\n**Related**: Existing tests cover writer/parser consistency for canonical writer output (`crates/bones-core/tests/tsjson_parse.rs:1013-1021`) and hash mismatch for changed payloads, but there is no coverage for non-canonical JSON bytes with a canonical hash.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","logic-error","data-integrity","hash"],"size":"s","title":"Parser verifies event hash against canonicalized payload instead of line bytes"}	blake3:tVrOaGu5oM2UDXlWAXaqYsnpDiEAte4CRnAxyLBaEa0
1777330109569419	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE32Qw		item.create	bn-296y	{"description":"**File**: crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/undo.rs:266-373, crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/undo.rs:473-494, crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/undo.rs:555-579\n\n**Issue**: `bn undo` converts operational failures during compensating-event emission into `skipped: true` result rows and then returns `Ok(())`, so callers can receive a successful exit status even though no undo event was written.\n\n**Root Cause**: `emit_compensating_event` uses the same `UndoEventResult { skipped: true }` shape for expected semantic skips and for infrastructure failures such as lock acquisition, shard rotation, timestamp allocation, ITC assignment, serialization, and append failure. The public `run_undo` render paths do not inspect the skip reason or convert those write-path failures back into an error.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (automation can treat a failed undo as successful)\n- Scope: Both `bn undo --event <hash>` and `bn undo <id> --last N`\n- Reproducibility: 100% when any write-path operation inside `emit_compensating_event` fails after the target event has been selected\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\n// crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/undo.rs:266-353\nlet _lock = match ShardLock::acquire(&lock_path, Duration::from_secs(5)) {\n    Ok(l) => l,\n    Err(e) => {\n        return UndoEventResult {\n            original_hash: original.event_hash.clone(),\n            original_type: original.event_type.as_str().to_string(),\n            compensating_hash: None,\n            compensating_type: Some(comp_type),\n            skipped: true,\n            skip_reason: Some(format!(\"failed to acquire lock: {e}\")),\n            dry_run: false,\n        };\n    }\n};\n...\nif let Err(e) = shard_mgr.append_raw(year, month, &line) {\n    return UndoEventResult {\n        original_hash: original.event_hash.clone(),\n        original_type: original.event_type.as_str().to_string(),\n        compensating_hash: None,\n        compensating_type: Some(comp_type),\n        skipped: true,\n        skip_reason: Some(format!(\"failed to append event: {e}\")),\n        dry_run: false,\n    };\n}\n```\n\nThe command then only renders the result and returns the render result:\n```rust\n// crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/undo.rs:555-579\nrender(output, &output_payload, |o, w| {\n    for r in &o.results {\n        if r.skipped {\n            writeln!(w, \"⚠  skipped {} [{}]: {}\", ...)?;\n        } else {\n            writeln!(w, \"{}✓ undid {} via {} ...\", ...)?;\n        }\n    }\n    Ok(())\n})\n```\n\n**Context**: The e2e coverage checks the happy path and asserts that successful undos are not skipped (`crates/bones-cli/tests/e2e_safety.rs:190-229`, `crates/bones-cli/tests/e2e_safety.rs:260-288`), but it does not exercise lock, append, timestamp, or serialization failures. Other write commands such as delete collect failures and return an error when any item fails (`crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/delete.rs:315-320`).\n\n**Related**: Semantic grow-only undo skips are expected for comments/compact/snapshot/redact (`crates/bones-core/src/undo.rs:17-21`); this issue is specifically about infrastructure failures being represented with the same non-fatal result shape.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","error-handling","data-integrity"],"size":"s","title":"bn undo reports success when compensating event writes fail"}	blake3:kuK7Z70-5A6R9I7TeKLCTMnvFIx2sncm5o7oRhRu5Es
1777330127529937	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE32gw		item.create	bn-3jzf	{"description":"**File**: crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/import.rs:441-509\n\n**Issue**: JSONL import skips malformed JSON syntax but aborts the whole command on invalid item IDs, event types, or payload schemas, after any prior valid lines have already been appended.\n\n**Root Cause**: The import loop only handles `serde_json::from_str` errors by incrementing `skipped_invalid` and continuing. Subsequent per-record validation uses `?`/`with_context`, which exits `run_jsonl_import` immediately. Because each valid record is appended before the next line is validated, an invalid later record leaves a partial import without rendering the summary counters.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (partial import state with failed command and incomplete machine-readable summary)\n- Scope: `bn import --jsonl` and `bn data import --jsonl`\n- Reproducibility: 100% for a JSONL file containing one valid event followed by a syntactically valid JSON object with an invalid `item_id`, unknown `type`, or schema-incompatible `data`\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\n// crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/import.rs:449-455\nlet record: JsonlEventRecord = match serde_json::from_str(&raw) {\n    Ok(record) => record,\n    Err(err) => {\n        report.skipped_invalid += 1;\n        eprintln!(\"skip line {line_no}: invalid JSON - {err}\");\n        continue;\n    }\n};\n\n// crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/import.rs:458-466\nlet item_id = ItemId::parse(&record.item_id)\n    .with_context(|| format!(\"line {line_no}: invalid item_id '{}'\", record.item_id))?;\n\nlet event_type = record.event_type.parse::<EventType>().with_context(|| {\n    format!(\"line {line_no}: unknown event type '{}'\", record.event_type)\n})?;\n\nlet data = EventData::deserialize_for(event_type, &record.data.to_string())\n    .with_context(|| format!(\"line {line_no}: invalid data payload\"))?;\n```\n\nValid records are appended inside the same loop before later records are checked:\n```rust\n// crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/import.rs:495-508\nshard_manager\n    .append_raw(year, month, &line)\n    .context(\"failed to append JSONL import event\")?;\n...\nreport.imported += 1;\n```\n\n**Context**: Error-path tests document graceful skipping for malformed JSON syntax (`crates/bones-cli/tests/e2e_reporting.rs:545-612`), and roundtrip import tests rebuild afterward to consume appended events (`crates/bones-cli/tests/e2e_reporting.rs:340-489`). There is no test for syntactically valid but semantically invalid JSONL records, which take a different code path from malformed JSON.\n\n**Related**: The summary shape has a `skipped_invalid` field (`crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/import.rs:406-414`), but that counter only covers JSON parse failures in the current loop.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","error-handling","data-integrity"],"size":"s","title":"JSONL import aborts on invalid record fields after partial append"}	blake3:XrgFrsm3rm8dhI_gQWw8NLdF7gmd1rd2ecXSg-RgelE
